# Git commits — no AI/tool footers

Do **not** add any of the following to commit messages (subject, body, or footer):

- `Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>` or any Co-Authored-By line for assistants
- `Made-with: Cursor` or similar tool branding lines

Use only conventional subject/body that describe the actual change.

## Cursor / Git for Windows

If commit messages still gain a `Made-with: Cursor` line, the `Git\cmd\git.exe` shim may be wrapping commits in this environment. Prefer `Git\mingw64\bin\git.exe` for `commit` / `commit --amend`, or strip the footer and amend using plumbing (`git commit-tree` + `reset`).
